[http://www.flickr.com/photos/jarruzza] Amazing! What a great connection. [http://www.flickr.com/photos/beachcomberaustralia] Aha! Beachcomber you were, as always, on the right track. Check out this <a href="http://www.daao.org.au/bio/charles-percy-pickering/biography/" rel="nofollow">bio</a> of Pickering on the Design &amp; Art Australia website. Quote:

&quot;Under the direction of Colonial Architect James Barnet, Pickering was commissioned by the New South Wales government in January 1871 to prepare 'a number of photographic views of Sydney and its suburbs’ for the forthcoming London International Exhibition.&quot;

Here is the <a href="http://acms.sl.nsw.gov.au/album/albumView.aspx?acmsID=442753&amp;itemID=823409" rel="nofollow">album</a> 'Photographs of Public and Other Buildings, &amp;c. Taken by Authority of the Government of New South Wales, at the Request of the Secretary of State for the Colonies'.
